# Spider Chemosensation — *Argiope bruennichi* CR Gene Repository

> Companion repository to **Montes-Ortiz et al.** — *Receptor expansion and appendage specialization reveal extensive complexity in spider chemosensation*

---

## Overview

This repository contains all scripts used for the identification, curation, and expression profiling of chemosensory receptor (CR) gene families in the wasp spider *Argiope bruennichi*. It covers four CR families: ionotropic glutamate receptors / ionotropic receptors (IRs/iGluRs), gustatory receptors (GRs), transient receptor potential channels (TRPs), and pickpocket receptors (PPKs).

---

## Repository Structure

```
.
├── General analysis/
│   ├── 01_transcriptome_assembly/     # QC, trimming, genome-guided and de novo assembly
│   ├── 02_cr_annotation/              # InterProScan, BLAST, domain-based curation
│   ├── 03_phylogenetics/              # MAFFT alignment, IQ-TREE, iTOL annotation
│   ├── 04_chromosome_mapping/         # Miniprot mapping, MG2C visualization
│   └── 05_expression/                 # Kallisto quantification, DESeq2 analysis
│
├── misc/
│   └── data_management/               # Utility scripts for file handling, format conversion
│                                      # and data cleaning (e.g. KallistoToDeseq2.py)
│
├── guide/
│   └── analysis_walkthrough.md        # Step-by-step guide to reproduce the full analysis
│
└── README.md
```

---

## Analysis Modules

| Step | Description | Language |
|------|-------------|----------|
| Transcriptome assembly | FastQC, TrimGalore, HISAT2, StringTie2, Trinity, BUSCO | Bash |
| CR annotation | InterProScan, BLASTP/tBLASTn, CD-HIT, CLANS clustering | Bash / Python |
| Phylogenetic analysis | MAFFT alignment, IQ-TREE tree inference, iTOL visualization | Bash |
| Chromosome mapping | Miniprot, Samtools, MG2C | Bash |
| Expression analysis | Kallisto quantification, DESeq2, z-score heatmaps, volcano plots | R / Python |

---

## Dependencies

### Bioinformatics tools
- FastQC v0.11.9
- TrimGalore v0.6.1
- Kraken2
- HISAT2 v2.2.1 / STAR v2.7.11a
- StringTie2 v2.1.4
- Trinity v2.9.1
- TransDecoder
- CD-HIT
- BUSCO v5.2.2 (`arachnida_odb10`)
- InterProScan v5 (with Pfam, PANTHER, TMHMM, Phobius)
- BLAST+
- MAFFT v7
- IQ-TREE2
- Miniprot
- Samtools v1.9
- Kallisto v0.48.0

### R packages
- `DESeq2` v1.42.1
- `ggplot2`
- `pheatmap`

---

## Reference Genome

All analyses are based on the chromosome-level *A. bruennichi* genome assembly:
- **Accession:** GCA_947563725.1
- **Reference:** Sheffer et al. (2021) *GigaScience*, https://doi.org/10.1093/gigascience/giaa148

